    "Since the training datasets predominantly consist of general videos, current T2V models struggle to produce videos depicting complex phenomena like seed germination, ice melting, or flower TABLE 1: Comparison of the characteristics of our Chrono-Magic benchmark with existing time-lapse datasets.",
    "We compare time-lapse video characteristics in terms of physics, persistence, and variation.",
    "Dataset Strong Physics High Persistence VariationSky Time-Lapse [7] Time-Lapse-D [8] ChronoMagic blooming, which are characterized by minimal physical content, brief duration, and limited variation.Compared to general videos, we have observed a category of videos that typically encompasses the subject's entire transformation process, thus addressing the inherent limitations of the former.",
